HEADWORD: intestable
<hw>in*tes"ta*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>intestabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>intestable</ets>. See <er>In-</er>
not, and <er>Testable</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Not capable of
making a will; not legally qualified or competent to make a
testament.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
